long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 4494 screen shot
Steps to reproduce: 1. Search for something in some project X 2. Let's display result (best reproducible on output with one result) 3. Un-click the project X in 'Project list' 4. Search again
Expected result: No project selected, an error is displayed.
Actual result: Search result is duplicated, see attached screen shot.
Used software: OpenGrok 0.10, Apache Tomcat 6.0.29, Sun Java 6 1.6.0_20-b02, Debian GNU/Linux 5.0, Mac OS X 10.6.6, Safari 5.0.3

cannot reproduce oddly enough if I select no project and do search it will search again with the same project (since it remembers it from a cookie)
so I am wondering on how did you bypass the cookie :)

I am able to reproduce duplicated results if I add a project twice in the URL. That would mean
...&project=linux-2.6.32.27&project=linux-2.6.32.27&...
or
...&project=linux-2.6.32.27,linux-2.6.32.27&...
in the URL (same result should be seen if it's duplicated in the cookie, but I didn't try that).
We could of course make the webapp de-duplicate project references in the URL and the cookie, but that still leaves us with the question how did it get duplicated in the first place. I did some code inspection, but nothing jumped at me.
